Important UI rules
If reconId is null, UI treats it as day-level cost report.
If reconId is populated, UI treats it as single recon cost report.
UI does not currently use “cost per successful recon” unless backend provides a supported field.
Do not return zero cost unless truly unavailable.
If cost data is unavailable, return:
{
  "available": false,
  "reasonIfUnavailable": "Cost data not available for this business date"
}
General Rules for Both Agents
Always return a meaningful answer.
Keep answer concise, operational, and human readable.
toolResponse.result must contain structured data for UI.
Avoid placeholder strings like "string" or "uuid".
Dates should be ISO-8601 UTC.
Arrays can be empty, but do not omit required top-level fields.
If no tool is called, return only answer; UI will show the generic AI Answer screen.
toolResponse may be either an object or escaped JSON string, but object is preferred.
Avoid frontend-derived narratives. Backend should provide facts, evidence, and recommendation text.
